  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study assesses the effect of Ritalin on working memory,attention,and decision-making
      measures in adults with ADHD and compares it to its effect on healthy adults, in a
      double-blind crossover design.We hypothesize that Ritalin will result in better performance
      in all measures,and that the improvement will be greater in the ADHD group.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
